<div id="home-guestScreen" class="guestScreen">
    <main class="hero flex">

        <div class="hero__taglineWrap">
            <h1 class="hero__tagline">We care<br /> about your time.</h1>
            <p class="hero__subTagLine">And will help you save it by providing quality notes, that are easy to refer and
                understand.</p>

            <button type="button" class="hero__cta btn btn--accent btn--large" data-trigger-type="add"
                data-trigger-target="loginOptions" data-trigger-action="loginOptions--visible">Let's NoteIT <i
                    class="fas fa-sign-in-alt btn__icon"></i></button>
        </div>

        <div class="hero__mockupWrap">
            <img src="/images/notesScreen.png" alt="notes screen sample" class="hero__mockup">
            <i class="fas fa-play font-3x desktop"></i>
        </div>


    </main>

    <section class="info">

        <div class="info__detailsWrap">
            <h2 class="info__heading heading heading--white">What is NoteIT ?</h2>
            <div class="info__details">
                <p>Being a student, its pretty challenging to prepare "well organized" notes.</p>
                <p>Maybe because of,</p>
                <ul class="info__list">
                    <li>lack of time,</li>
                    <li>"confusion" regarding the topic or,</li>
                    <li>lack of "good" reference.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Whatever the reason is, most of us will agree that its pretty difficult to prepare "organized" and
                    "readable"
                    notes. </p>

                <h3>That is the reason why we created NoteIT.</h3>
                <p>We will provide well organized notes that are easy to read and understand, based on the exact
                    syllabus
                    provided
                    by the TU.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

    </section>

    <section class="processContainer">
        <h2 class="heading">This is how it works</h2>

        <div class="processContainer__processWrap flex centerContents flex--cr flex--wrap">
            <div class="processContainer__process card" data-process-no="1">
                <h3>Sign up for an account</h3>
                <p>You can easily sign up via "Facebook" or "Google" and be a member of NoteIT.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="processContainer__process card" data-process-no="2">
                <h3>Get a list of available notes</h3>
                <p>We will send you a list of notes based on your faculty and semester.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="processContainer__process card" data-process-no="3">
                <h3>View the notes</h3>
                <p>Easily view and read notes on up to three different device(s), using the same account.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="processContainer__process card" data-process-no="4">
                <h3>Save the notes</h3>
                <p>You can "save" the notes into your account to have easy access later on.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="processContainer__process card" data-process-no="5">
                <h3>Ask questions</h3>
                <p>Clear your confusions by chatting with the "note contributor" themselves.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>